videos.title: Ryan Interviews Health care Expert About Coronavirus. Let's Learn How we can help each other.
videos.description:
Ryan and his parents speak with leading U.S. health care expert Andy Slavitt to ask questions about Coronavirus to help kids like himself to better understand the pandemic and how they can protect themselves and others.
On behalf of the whole family, we also want to give a HUGE THANKS to all the brave first responders on the front lines helping communities fight the pandemic across the nation. We’re donating $500,000 to the First Responders Children’s Foundation to help with the organization’s COVID-19 relief efforts which provides support to the families of paramedics, police officers, firefighters and medical professionals. More information can be found at www.1strcf.org!
 
All of us at Ryan’s World encourage you to help where you can by checking in on loved ones and being kind to everyone, especially during this time. And remember, #StayHome, stay happy and rise up!

videos.description:
Kids science experiment with Skittles makes an awesome skittles rainbow effect! This is a great DIY Skittles experiment that every parent should do with their kids. Also, a great science fair project or STEM Activity to do with your kids if you are looking for ideas. As the sugar starts dissolving off of the Skittles candy the "Sugar rich" water is much denser than the normal water and sinks to the bottom of the plate. As the colored sugar moves down the plate it makes a great rainbow effect for the kids to enjoy!

#STEMActivities

- A white plate (to better see the colors)

videos.title: Denser Than You Think - Science Experiment
videos.description:
Simple density science experiment that you can try at home to see how liquids and objects with different densities behave. By dropping items with different densities into the glass, we can see which fluids are denser than them.

videos.title: Experimenting with Diffusion! 🧬 | ELEVERSE with Professor World
videos.description:
Welcome back to ELEVERSE with Professor World! Each episode, Professor World and his friends will dive deep on a science topic explored in the latest Elemon adventure. This week is all about the water power of DIFFUSION. 
 
Hang out with Ryan, Emma, and Kate as they get a visit from their favorite water-type Elemon, Aquro! Aquro helps them learn all about the properties of water, including DIFFUSION. Be sure to stick around to the end when Ryan and his family perform some awesome, colorful, diffusion experiments, then grab an adult so you can try them out yourself at home! 
 
And if you haven’t already, check out all the latest Elemon adventures here! https://www.youtube.com/@ElemonSeries

videos.title: Learn All About WATER💧 | ELEVERSE with Professor World
videos.description:
Welcome to the first ever episode of ELEVERSE with Professor World! In this new series, Ryan will join his friends from the world of Elemon! Together, they’ll explore topics related to the latest Elemon adventures! 
 
This week, Ryan’s learning all about WATER. He’ll find out how atoms come together to make elements, including H20, or water! Along the way, he’ll be joined by Aquro, a water-type Elemon, and his friend Professor World, who’s experimenting with water pressure to build a GIANT ROBOTIC ARM! 
 
Remember to check out all the latest episodes of Elemon here! https://www.youtube.com/@ElemonSeries

videos.title: Ryan Interviews Health care Expert About Coronavirus. Let's Learn How we can help each other.
videos.description:
Ryan and his parents speak with leading U.S. health care expert Andy Slavitt to ask questions about Coronavirus to help kids like himself to better understand the pandemic and how they can protect themselves and others.
On behalf of the whole family, we also want to give a HUGE THANKS to all the brave first responders on the front lines helping communities fight the pandemic across the nation. We’re donating $500,000 to the First Responders Children’s Foundation to help with the organization’s COVID-19 relief efforts which provides support to the families of paramedics, police officers, firefighters and medical professionals. More information can be found at www.1strcf.org!
 
All of us at Ryan’s World encourage you to help where you can by checking in on loved ones and being kind to everyone, especially during this time. And remember, #StayHome, stay happy and rise up!

Eggs go on sale Thursday, November 22nd starting at 6 PM local time or 6 PM east coast standard time online. The eggs are available while supplies last.
Every egg includes one (1) Game Card with a unique Promo Code which you can use to enter the Instant Win Game for the chance to WIN A PLAYDATE WITH RYAN!  [Hold up the game card]. One lucky grand prize winner will win a trip for (4) people, courtesy of Frontier Airlines, to Los Angeles where you’ll get to meet Ryan at pocket.watch studios! Grand prize winner will also get tickets to Universal Studios Hollywood, a collection of toys worth $300, Halos delivered to their home, and a collectible Golden Ryan figure.  

If you don’t win the grand prize, there are also hundreds of other prizes you can win and a special video message for everyone who enters. You can only access the video by entering the Promo Code listed on your game card.  

NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. A PURCHASE DOES NOT INCREASE YOUR CHANCES OF WINNING. To obtain a free game card via the U.S. Mail, send a self-addressed stamped envelope to: Play Date with Ryan Game Card Request, c/o Centra 360, 1400 Old Country Road, Suite 306, Westbury, NY 11590. Vermont residents may omit return postage. All Game Card requests must be postmarked by January 31, 2019 and received by February 7, 2019. Game ends on January 31, 2019 and is open to legal residents of the 50 United States an District of Columbia who are at least 18 years of age or older. Void where prohibited. videos.title: Ryan Interviews Health care Expert About Coronavirus. Let's Learn How we can help each other.
videos.description:
Ryan and his parents speak with leading U.S. health care expert Andy Slavitt to ask questions about Coronavirus to help kids like himself to better understand the pandemic and how they can protect themselves and others.
On behalf of the whole family, we also want to give a HUGE THANKS to all the brave first responders on the front lines helping communities fight the pandemic across the nation. We’re donating $500,000 to the First Responders Children’s Foundation to help with the organization’s COVID-19 relief efforts which provides support to the families of paramedics, police officers, firefighters and medical professionals. More information can be found at www.1strcf.org!
 
All of us at Ryan’s World encourage you to help where you can by checking in on loved ones and being kind to everyone, especially during this time. And remember, #StayHome, stay happy and rise up!

videos.description:

All 30 episodes of Elemon series are available on Kidoodle.TV Now!  @KidoodleTV  
You can check out Elemon episodes on Kidoodle.TV from the link below. 
https://kidoodle.tv/2898/elemon?category=WhatsNEW

 Leo’s sister Ela has a BIG one: she LOVES cute things! But she can’t let Leo know that- it would ruin her tough girl image! So, Ela decides to make a new, adorable Elemon, just for herself! But can she be a good friend to her new Elemon without being true to herself first?

videos.title: Ryan Interviews Health care Expert About Coronavirus. Let's Learn How we can help each other.
videos.description:
Ryan and his parents speak with leading U.S. health care expert Andy Slavitt to ask questions about Coronavirus to help kids like himself to better understand the pandemic and how they can protect themselves and others.
On behalf of the whole family, we also want to give a HUGE THANKS to all the brave first responders on the front lines helping communities fight the pandemic across the nation. We’re donating $500,000 to the First Responders Children’s Foundation to help with the organization’s COVID-19 relief efforts which provides support to the families of paramedics, police officers, firefighters and medical professionals. More information can be found at www.1strcf.org!
 
All of us at Ryan’s World encourage you to help where you can by checking in on loved ones and being kind to everyone, especially during this time. And remember, #StayHome, stay happy and rise up!
